<concept id="bill_cycle_calendar">
    <title>Bill Cycle Calendar</title>
    <conbody>
        <section id="section_khh_n5y_ymb">
            <title>Overview</title>
            <p>Bill cycle calendar provides flexibility to define a period length for lifecyle such
                that the period difference between two periodic events is not fixed. It can be
                defined manually, and on basis of this value the next bill cycle occurs.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="section_mkf_hvy_ymb">
            <title>Configuration</title>
            <p>Log into the SM GUI and navigate to <uicontrol>Policy &amp; Charging
                    Configuration</uicontrol> &gt; <uicontrol>COMMON</uicontrol>. Select
                    <uicontrol>Bill Cycle Calendar</uicontrol> from the hamburger menu (<image
                    href="../images/img9yz-09126-ug01-pczza-sp1-hamburgermenu_default.png"
                    scale="40" id="image_pgk_hvy_ymb"/>). To define a new calendar, click <image
                    href="../images/img9yz-09126-ug01-pczza-sp1-add_button_default.png" scale="45"
                    id="image_qgk_hvy_ymb"/> and provide the details as described in the following
                table.</p>
