                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>Periodic Dates</entry>
                            <entry>This fiekd includes all the defined period dates.<p>Initially,
                                    there is option to add one date. Click <b>ADD DATE</b> to add
                                    more dates. The dates are added using a calendar or MM/DD/YYYY
                                    format.</p>Once the bill cycle calendar is saved, the dates
                                already added cannot be changed during an update. However, new dates
                                can be added.<p>The dates must be in ascending order.</p>The list
                                can contain a maximum of 50 dates. After 50 dates are defined, if a
                                new date is added, the earliest date is removed from the
                                list.</entry>
                            <entry>List (size 50)</entry>
                            <entry>Optional</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </section>
